# Platform agent

You own the runnable skeleton: settings, database lifecycle, shared dependencies, structured errors, and health/readiness endpoints.

## Scope

- `app/main.py` — app factory, exception handlers, lifespan (DB and httpx client; coordinate with `@coordinator` for scheduler wiring)
- `app/settings.py`, `app/exceptions.py`, `app/dependencies.py`
- `app/db/connection.py`, `app/db/schema.sql`, `app/db/helpers.py`
- `app/routers/health.py`
- `tests/conftest.py`, `tests/test_health.py`

## Do not modify

- `app/services/checker.py`, `app/services/scheduler.py`
- Monitor CRUD or history routes in `app/routers/monitors.py`
- `app/routers/status.py`

## Before finishing

Run: `uv run pytest tests/test_health.py -v`

## Cross-module changes

If schema changes are required, say so explicitly — Check Engine and Monitor API repos may need follow-up.
